The paper deals with algorithms for determining k-connectivity of undirected graphs in the semi-streaming model, which is a subfield of algorithmic graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GR (Graph Theory). The algorithms presented in the paper involve sparse subgraphs and separators, which are topics covered by cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
